lombok-pg is a collection of extensions to lombok (https://github.com/rzwitserloot/lombok)
distrubuted together with lombok in one spice package.
The lombok version lombok-pg is based on is usaually pretty much up to date, so you
can do all the funky stuff lombok offers and a bit more.

The current extensions are:

  - @AutoGenMethodStub
  - @Builder and @BuilderExtension
  - @DoPrivileged
  - @FluentSetter
  - @ListenerSupport
  - @WriteLock, @ReadLock, @Await, @Signal, @AwaitBeforeAndSignalAfter
  - @Rethrow, @Rethrows
  - @Singleton
  - @SwingInvokeLater and @SwingInvokeAndWait
  - @VisibleForTesting
  - Interfaces lombok.Application and lombok.JVMAgent (Entrypoint Generation)
  - tuple(var1, var2, ...) = tuple(expr1, expr2, ...) - tuple assignment
  - with(object, expr1, expr2, ...)
  - yield(object)

If you like to try lombok-pg out, grab a copy over here:
http://cloud.github.com/downloads/peichhorn/lombok-pg/lombok-pg-0.10.0-BETA2-HEAD.jar

If don't know where to start or how to use lombok-pg, you might want to
try lombok out first and read this:
http://projectlombok.org/features/index.html

You can also find a feature documentation of lombok-pg here:
http://peichhorn.github.com/lombok-pg/
